This paper deals with improving the quality of ontology-based knowledge bases (KBs) like DBpedia, which involves using techniques from artificial intelligence (AI) and machine learning (ML) to predict relevant entities and types. Therefore, cs.AI is the most likely sub-category. The paper also deals with issues related to databases (cs.DB) and information retrieval (cs.IR), as it aims to improve the usefulness and usability of KBs. The use of machine learning also suggests a connection to the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper deals with semantic integration (cs.SI) of KBs, which is another relevant sub-category.
